Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
getSdpGroupAttribute(25.10)                        getSdpGroupAttribute(25.10)

Name
       getSdpGroupAttribute  -  Displays the current values of various attrib-
       utes of the SDP group specified with -name

Syntax
       getSdpGroupAttribute

       [-help]

       [-flip]

        [-justifyBy]

        -name <sdp_name>

        [-orient]

       [-origin]

       [-padding]

       [-skipSpace]

       [-type]

       Displays the current values of various  attributes  of  the  SDP  group
       specified with -name. If you do not specify any parameter except -name,
       getSdpGroupAttribute  returns  information on all of the setSdpGroupAt-
       tribute parameters for the SDP group specified with -name.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each getSdpGroupAttribute parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man getSdpGroupAttribute.

       -flip  Returns the flip information of the specified SDP group.

       -justifyBy
              Returns the anchor point used to align the specified SDP group.

       -name <sdp_name>
              Specifies the name of the SDP for you which you want to retrieve
              settings. This parameter is mandatory.

       <-orient>
              Returns the orientation of the specified SDP group.

       -origin
              Returns the location of the top SDP group.

       -padding
              Returns the padding of the top sdp object.

       -skipSpace
              Returns the spacing pattern of the specified SDP group.

       -type  Returns the type of the specified SDP group.

Example
              * The following command returns information on all of the  setS-
                dpGroupAttribute parameters for the SDP group group2:

                innovus 16> getSdpGroupAttribute -name group2

                {flip   NONE}  {justifyBy  SW}  {orient  R0}  {origin  (700.26
                649.04)} {skipSpace {0 0 0 0 0 0 }} {type column}

